title: Badi MASTER
description: Song 2 from Shade of the Tree of Life
notes:
Shade of the Tree of Life is five songs inspired by the sacred Writings and history of the Bah√° º√≠ Faith. The lyrics are drawn from the rich imagery and metaphors found in sacred scriptures. The album title Shade of the Tree of Life is from a passage in The Hidden Words of Bah√°‚Äôu‚Äôll√°h. It recalls a time at the dawn of consciousness when we gathered in the divine Presence beneath the shade of the Tree of Life sanctified above the limitations of time and space. From the divine Light we were born and to the divine Light we return.

Once Upon a Dream takes the listener on a voyage in the company of an angelic being to a realm of light beyond the senses where the knowledge of all things is revealed to the pure and open heart. The voyager must then carry the light back to this world of rampant tyranny and hatred where the oppressors of the earth, heedless, continue to march toward their own destruction. Yet, while the maelstrom rages below, a vision of peace and beauty awakens in the voyager who remembers a future Golden Age promised in sacred scriptures and traditions.
   
In the Fire of Your Love is a celebration of our return to the Source of all life after enduring the manifold trials and tribulation of this material world. From the clay of love we were molded and to the shelter of love we return. 

Break Off Your Chains is an exhortation to break the bonds of our earthly limitations, take the hands of our brothers and sisters, unleash the power of the divine light we carry within, turn the tide of darkness and illuminate the world.  

Fire of the Worlds was inspired by The Fire Tablet of Bah√°‚Äôu‚Äôll√°h. It is a cry from the heart for divine assistance and an expression of resolve to carry the light forward despite the ascendency of the forces of oppression and darkness. 

Bad√≠ is an elegy for a fallen soldier in the Army of Light. It is an historical ballad that retraces the steps of a young man who arose to serve the cause of Bah√° ºu'll√°h. With unshakable resolve, he set out on a perilous journey to carry a letter Bah√° ºu'll√°h had written from his prison cell to the Shah of Persia. In this letter, Bah√° ºu'll√°h admonishes the Shah to place the well being of his people above his own self interest, to seek wisdom and rule with justice. The Shah disdainfully rejects Bah√° ºu'll√°h's message and has the young man arrested. Despite three days of torture, Bad√≠‚Äôs spirit was unbroken.

I am grateful to my friends who made this production possible. My recording engineer Grey Bear Erickson enriched the sound with his instrumentals and postproduction talent. Sandy Hoover was a source of ongoing advice and encouragement and connected me with Grey Bear. Ashley Urban designed the graceful image of the phoenix embracing the Tree of Life. My voice teacher and confidence coach Nancy Bos gave me the tools to bring this project to completion. I am especially grateful to you, the listener, for listening to my songs.
